{{Infobox saint | name = Abhai (saint) | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | titles = Saint | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | venerated_in = Syriac Orthodox Church | beatified_date = | beatified_place = | beatified_by = | canonized_date = | canonized_place = | canonized_by = | major_shrine = | feast_day = July 15 and May 3 | attributes = | patronage = | issues = | suppressed_date = | suppressed_by = | quote = }}
'''Abhai''' is a [[saint]] of the [[Syriac Orthodox Church]]. He is said to have lived for 100 years. He is a [[patron saint]] against poisonous reptiles. His [[feast day]] is celebrated on July 15 and May 3. He is included in the ''[[Syrian Martyrology of Rabban Silba]]''.
Saint Abhai is not to be confused with the 4th-century Syriac martyr [[Abai (martyr)|Abai]].
