{{Portal|Anglicanism}}'''Joseph William Abbott'''  was [[Dean of Leighlin]] from 1912 until 1939.<ref>[[Crockford's Clerical Directory]] p1 Oxford, OUP, 1929</ref>

Bolton was educated at [[Trinity College, Dublin]] and [[ordained]] [[deacon]] in 1876 and [[priest]] in 1876. He began his ecclesiastical career with a [[Curate|curacy]] in [[Bilboa]]. He held [[Incumbent (ecclesiastical)|incumbencies]] in [[Old Leighlin]], [[Tullow]] and [[Courtown|Kiltennel]].<ref>{{cite news |title=New Dean of Leighlin |url=https://www.britishnewspaperarchive.co.uk/viewer/bl/0001384/19121223/155/0009 |accessdate=27 July 2018 |work=Dublin Daily Express |date=23 December 1912 |ref=yes |page=9}}</ref>

He died on 25 April 1939.<ref>''Obituary'' [[The Times]] (London, England), Thursday, Apr 27, 1939; pg. 21; Issue 48290</ref>{{Failed verification|date=July 2018|reason=Not mentioned on this page or in any Times search}}

