{{Infobox person | name = Karpal Kaur Sandhu | image = | birth_date = 1943 | birth_place = Zanzibar | death_date = 4 November 1973 | death_place = Walthamstow | death_cause = murdered | occupation = Police Officer | employer = Metropolitan Police Service | known_for = first female Asian police officer }}
'''Karpal Kaur Sandhu''' was the first female Asian police officer in the world. She served in the [[Metropolitan Police Service]] from 1971 to 1973.
== History == Sandhu was born in [[Zanzibar]] in 1943, before moving to Britain in 1962 and becoming a nurse.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-london-12330579|title=Call to honour an Asian 'pioneer'|last=Neiyyar|first=Dil|date=2011-02-01|work=BBC News|access-date=2017-11-05|language=en-GB}}</ref> She joined the [[Metropolitan Police Service]] on 1 February 1971, serving first in [[Hornsey]], then in [[Walthamstow]] and [[Leyton]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.guardian-series.co.uk/news/8804149.HISTORY__Met_Police_marks_40th_anniversary_of_first_female_Asian_officer/|title=HISTORY: Met Police marks 40th anniversary of first female Asian officer|last=Hardy|first=Clare|date=|website=East London and West Essex Guardian Series|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-11-05}}</ref> Her date of joining made her the first female Asian police officer in the world, beating India's [[Kiran Bedi]] by just over one year.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/law-and-order/9024974/Life-as-an-ethnic-minority-police-officer.html|title=Life as an ethnic minority police officer|last=Llewellyn|first=Julia|date=2012|access-date=2017-11-05|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=l5rVBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA15&lpg=PA15&dq=%22Karpal+Kaur+Sandhu%22&source=bl&ots=9o-lHVKAwf&sig=27Bu1ADF8EF-mzxvJMRe3fMO45I&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjjrrDVr6bXAhXDuRoKHZ7BDck4ChDoAQgtMAE#v=onepage&q=%22Karpal%20Kaur%20Sandhu%22&f=false|title=Women Police Unfurled in Pakistan: Perspective, Status and Prospective|last=Arain|first=Saima Manzoor|date=2014-06-22|publisher=Lulu.com|isbn=9781312276246|language=en}}</ref>{{Self-published inline|date=December 2017}}
Sandhu died in the line of duty on 4 November 1973. Her husband did not agree with her becoming a police officer, and he had taken their two children to India. However, he returned to the UK and confronted her outside her house in Chelmsford Road, Walthamstow.<ref name=":0" /> When her husband attacked her, she recalled herself to duty in order to arrest him, but he stabbed her in the neck. In March 1974 he was found guilty of her murder.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.policememorial.org.uk/index.php?page=metropolitan-police|title=Police Roll of Honour Trust|last=|first=|date=|website=www.policememorial.org.uk|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-11-05}}</ref>
