{{About|the Consul of the Republic|the city in Paraguay|Mariano Roque Alonso, Paraguay}}

'''Mariano Roque Alonso Romero''' (1792–1853)<ref>{{cite book |last1=Nickson |first1=R. Andrew |title=Historical Dictionary of Paraguay |date=2015 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=9780810879645 |page=41 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-Ji-CQAAQBAJ&pg=PA41 |accessdate=15 June 2018 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |editor1-last=Kinsbruner |editor1-first=Jay |title=Encyclopedia of Latin American History and Culture |date=2008 |publisher=Charles Scribner's Sons}}</ref> was [[List of Presidents of Paraguay|President of the Provisional Junta]] of [[Paraguay]] from 9 February 1841 to 14 March 1841. On 14 March 1841 he established a government ruling jointly with [[Carlos Antonio López]] and they both styled themselves "consuls of the republic". After three years of this arrangement, on 13 March 1844, Roque Alonzo resigned and López became the sole ruler of the country.

